Would that I could fall Myself before God / Would that my History were transfix’d in His eye – Metrophanes of Crete, 233 BCE, Cosmologies of Man

Translated by James Sheldrake, 1790

”You might try then, as I did, to find a sky so full of stars it will blind you again. Only no sky can blind you now. Even with all that iridescent magic up there, your eye will no longer linger on the light, it will no longer trace constellations. You’ll care only about the darkness and you’ll watch it for hours, for days, maybe even years, trying in vain to believe you’re some kind of indispensable, universe-appointed sentinel, as if just by looking you could actually keep it all at bay. It will get so bad you’ll be afraid to look away, you’ll be afraid to sleep. (…) And then the nightmares will begin.” – Mark Z. Danielewski, House of Leaves

 - SCP-001: spikebrennan's Proposal

Special thanks to pastarasta1 for enthusiasm and nagging.

Special thanks to W Asriel for technical help.

The photo, video, and audio are by me. The music features a sample of the free to use piece “Camelot Monastery” by Darren Curtis. It has been heavily edited and distorted at points to imitate the music of György Ligeti. The video stars JEM.

Inspired by the films of David Lynch, Ingmar Bergman, and Stanley Kubrick. Inspired by the writings of Eben Alexander. Also based on a few true, but mundane, experiences.

Trigger warning for a mild jumpscare, discussion of sexual violence, depiction of domestic violence, and infrasound.





